# Figma -> Storybook Parity Gate (Global)

Use this process for every component/pattern mapping or visual implementation task.

## Mandatory Workflow

1. Build mapping first
   - Storybook source: `http://localhost:6006/index.json`
   - Figma source: `user-figma-console` tools only
   - Keep `FIGMA_STORYBOOK_MAPPING.md` and `design-mapping.json` updated

2. Extract exact Figma specs before coding
   - Pull node-level structure (layout, spacing, size, radius, stroke/fill vars)
   - Pull text specs (text style, size, line-height, color token)
   - Pull component-in-component usage (e.g., Button instance) and map to existing Storybook components

3. Reuse Storybook components, do not reinvent
   - If a component exists in Storybook, use it directly (props/variants only)
   - Do not recreate visuals with local CSS if a documented component already provides it

4. Token/style rules
   - No hardcoded visual values for color/spacing/radius/typography when token/style exists
   - Prefer existing typography utility classes over custom font declarations
   - Any exception must be explicitly justified and minimized

5. Parity audit required before completion
   - Produce a concise checklist per changed module:
     - Structure/hierarchy parity
     - Typography class parity
     - Color/stroke/fill token parity
     - Spacing/radius parity
     - Embedded component parity (Button, etc.)

## Stop Conditions (Do Not Proceed)

- Mapping between Figma node and Storybook story is ambiguous
- Required Storybook component exists but implementation uses custom substitute
- Typography is implemented with ad-hoc sizes despite existing text styles
